HARRISON

S'lI\FI" VVRl'l‘l{R

 

formers made Snow White extremely funny as
they changed aspects of it such as the genre,
the attitudes of the characters and its setting in
time.

Another game that amused me was the
dating game. In this game, one male and three
females volunteered to participate, but the guy
was not allowed to see what the girls looked
like until the end when he picked one. Each girl
was assigned a silly occupation to talk about
when trying to Win over the bach-
elor. What made it all the more
enjoyable was that the couple in
the end had to actually go out on
a date and tell about it at the next
Friday!

In addition to the games, there is also a
part called Showcase, where a person or group
(who signed up in advance) puts on a perfor-
mance. That night, a local group of musicians
was featured. Previous showcases included a
tap dancer, poetry readings, and stand-up
comedians. _

I was extremely impressed at the level of
talent on the parts of the people who performed
— they were funny and truly got into what
they were doing. Being a fairly shy person, I
admired how they could just get up in front of
a large group of people and "perform impro-
vised comedy. It amazes me how they make up
hilarious ideas right there on the spot, one story
after another. ’

Chris was one of the people who per-
formed and he told me that it feels really great
when you are up there in front of everyone.
Although I am sure that this is true, I can’t see
myself doing that —— I’d rather just watch.

I found myself laughing more in those two
hours that I had all week. When the evening
ended, I knew that I would be back sometime
and my friend deﬁnitely agreed. Irnprov is a
good change from the Friday night party scene
as it gives people the chance to get together and
laugh, something that we don’t see happening
enough.

Megan Harrison hopes to see everyone in the
basement of the Cathedral this Friday night.

